The TSIMMIS Approach to Mediation: Data Models and Languages TSIMMIS -- The Stanford-IBM Manager of Multiple Information Sources -- is a system for integrating information. It o ers a data model and a common query language that are designed to support the combining of information from many different sources. It also o ers tools for generating automatically the components that are needed to build systems for integrating information. In this paper we shall discuss the principal architectural features and their rationale.
